Title: Framework agreement procedure first stage
Description: The contracting process is the second stage of a framework agreement procedure. The related process is the contracting process that established the framework agreement.

Title: Planning process
Description: The related process is the planning process that planned the contracting process.

Title: Parent contract (for sub-contracts)
Description: The contracting process aims to conclude one or more sub-contracts. The related process is the contracting process that concluded the main contract.
Deprecation note: Deprecated because OCDS 1.2 describes a subcontract within its main contract, not within a separate contracting process.

Title: Successful process
Description: The contracting process aims to extend, renew, repeat or replace one or more contracts from the related contracting process.

Title: Unsuccessful process
Description: The contracting process is another attempt to conclude one or more contracts. The related process is the contracting process that attempted and failed to conclude the contracts previously.

Title: Sub-contract
Description: The related process might result in a sub-contract of this contract.
Deprecation note: Deprecated because OCDS 1.2 describes a subcontract within its main contract, not within a separate contracting process.

Title: Replacement process
Description: The related process might result in the replacement of this contract.
Deprecation note: Deprecated in favor of 'prior', because  OCDS 1.2 follows a "child refers to parent" approach to linking related processes.

Title: Renewal process
Description: The related process might result in the renewal of this contract.
Deprecation note: Deprecated in favor of 'prior', because OCDS 1.2 follows a "child refers to parent" approach to linking related processes.
